article.description: Justin Wright-Foreman scored 30 points that included a game-winning 3-point play with 16 seconds left to give Hofstra a 75-73 victory over Monmouth on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Wright-Foreman scores 30, leads Hofstra over Monmouth 75-73
article.linkText: Wright-Foreman scores 30, leads Hofstra over Monmouth 75-73
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. -- Justin Wright-Foreman scored 30 points that included a game-winning 3-point play with 16 seconds left to give Hofstra a 75-73 victory over Monmouth on Wednesday night. Hofstra (6-3) won its third straight while Monmouth (0-10) remains winless. Ray Salnave made two layups between Desure Buie's 3-pointer and Monmouth led 73-72 with 31 seconds to go. Wright-Foreman scored, and following a timeout, Louie Pillari missed a 3-pointer as time expired. Wright-Foreman was 10 of 23 from the floor and made four 3-pointers. Eli Pemberton added 14 points for the Pride. Buie hit two key 3-pointers in the second half and finished with nine points. Salnave scored 22 points and Deion Hammond had 14 for Monmouth. The duo made seven of the Hawks' eight 3-pointers. There were two ties and five lead changes in the final four minutes.
